    Returning Global Store Items

    The General Return Policy is applicable for all Amazon Global Store Products (“Product”). If the Product is eligible for a refund on return, you can choose to return the Product either through courier Pickup or Self-Return**

    Note: - Once the package is received at Amazon Export Sales LLC fulfillment center in the US, it takes 2 (two) business days for the refund to be processed and 2- 4 business days for the refund amount to reflect in your account. - If your return is due to an Amazon error you'll receive a full refund, else the shipping charges (onward & return) along with import fees will be deducted from your refund amount.

    From the manufacturer

    Do-It-All Screen

    The monitor for every side of life. Get work done without a PC, with the installed Microsoft Office 365, or by remote access to your office computer. Then switch to pure entertainment with the on-board one-stop entertainment system.

    UHD Resolution

    Great picture quality for work and play. With 4x the pixels of Full HD, the Smart Monitor delivers more screen space and life-like UHD images. By day, see more documents at once. And, in the evening, watch movies in cinematic 4K quality.

    Mobile meets big screen

    Wireless DeX unlocks a full PC experience, without any PC. Use mobile productivity apps, such as video conferencing, documents, and browsers, through just your monitor and phone. To see photos or watch movies on the big screen, just tap it with your phone using Tap View.

    Read more

    Smart TV Apps

    Binge watching got even easier. Access a bunch of entertainment apps, such as Netflix, YouTube, and Amazon Prime, without switching on your PC or laptop. The remote control and built-in speakers simplify your chill time..

    Work and learn from a distance

    Work seamlessly from anywhere. Boost your productivity with Remote Access features. Using the Office 365 suite, view and edit documents, and conveniently save them all on the cloud. Even while at home, Remote Access lets you work remotely on your school or office desktop

    Optimal brightness for any ambience

    Sensational picture, day or night. Surrounding light is detected by a sensor to adjust brightness automatically with Adaptive Picture. Even in broad daylight, watch dark, gritty dramas without squinting and straining your eyes to see the picture

    Read more

    Ultrawide Game View

    Keep your eye on the win. Adjust your screen to 21:9 to discover hidden areas in game scenes with Ultrawide Game View. Now when you play soccer games, see more of the pitch right up to the goalposts. And in driving games, get a natural and encompassing view of the road ahead

    Voice Assistant

    Your monitor listens to what you tell it. Switch between apps, control videos, and more through the Voice Assistant or SmartThings app

    USB Type C

    The USB type-C port enables you to power up, transmit data, and even send display signals between devices with just one connection. Its single connection architecture brings an enjoyable work environment that's both clutter-free and stress-free

    Read more

    Plug and see

    No more switching around. With Automatic Source Switch Plus, your monitor detects newly connected devices as soon they're plugged in, and displays the correct signal. No more searching for the right input on the menu.

    Connect with Airplay2

    With integrated AirPlay 2, use Apple devices to work and play on the big screen. Improve your workflow by creating a wireless dual monitor setup with your MacBook and Smart Monitor. When it's time to relax, effortlessly enjoy videos, music, photos, and more from your iPhone or iPad.

    Read more

    4.0 out of 5 stars Brightness is not an Issue but the VA Panel is.. (43" Model)
    Reviewed in India on 26 January 2022
    Style name: 43' Smart MonitorPattern name: 43" UHD MonitorVerified Purchase
    I use a LG LM7600 as TV for the past 10years. I don't know the type of panel being is used in that TV, but it doesn't become whitish when viewed even at any angle. But this monitor looks whitish when viewed from any angle but straight. But when using a monitor, the primary reason for which i bought this monitor, i always sit at 3ft away and exactly at the middle of the monitor, from which i don't have any issues.

    In most of the reviews, they talk about brightness as an issue being a VA Panel (but the monitor is so bright that, it might actually blind us in most of the default settings available especially while having a white background like excel or webpage in full screen). Except one reviewer by the name KLGadgetGuy, all others have reviewed only 32" but this guy actually reviewed 43" which i bought (in website i found that the 32" is 250nits whereas 300nits for 42")

    I went for this size from 22" Dual monitor setup mainly because of the price difference between 32" and 42" in a business price. Since in any monitor above 32" comes at 28% GST, this worked out to be just Rs4000 costlier than the 32" and the size also happens to be equivalent to 22"quad monitor. And, should admit that, the size is not intimidating. Got accustomed after a day of headache and eye strain, from day two i was absolutely fine using this. From my one week experience, 43in size is not an issue for the monitor (personally**).

    My advice would be, Please see the monitor at a store, connect it to your laptop.. But in my case, no dealer in and around Chennai had one to see it. Let alone the 43"Size none had a monitor of any size to see, all were TVs only. This is my first review and i'm writing this so that it would be helpful for making your purchase decision.

    Overall, a good product. Happy buying it.. If its not urgent check the pricing in price history and then buy it during festive deals.

    3.0 out of 5 stars May not good for most users
    Reviewed in India on 23 April 2022
    Style name: 43' Smart MonitorPattern name: 43" UHD MonitorVerified Purchase
    This review is for 43 inch version.
    After 3 months of usage this is what I feel.

    Pros:
    1. Screen quality is good. No complaints.
    2. It is equal to 4 X 21" monitor. It gives lot of real estate. For programming, you can see double the lines as 1080p monitor which is really good.
    3. Scrolling reduces into half in both vertically and horizontally.
    4. HDMI-ARC port is there for soundbars.
    5. Price - It is cheaper than other 43" monitors.

    Cons:
    1. It is not ergonomic. There is no height adjustable stand. So you have to adjust your chair or table to accommodate the monitor height which is really painful process. Not easy to find a stand for this size monitor in market.
    2. PIP and PBP are missing. For large size monitor, they will be really useful. For cost cutting, they removed this important feature.
    3. If you prefer to use it as TV, Ethernet port and audio out ports are missing (only WiFi for internet).
    4. Only 2 HDMI ports. Even budget TVs provide 3 HDMI ports.
    5. There is occasional black out. it shows refresh GIF for couple seconds. Not sure if it is software glitch.
    6. Speaker quality. It is usual budget TV speaker. Don't expect much. But it is acceptable.

    TV, Monitor hybrid option may not needed for most users. Samsung removed some features in both monitor and TV. You may not use any one option. So better not try to get both in one, unless that is your priority.

    If you are buying it for monitor purpose, better go with options like PIP, PBP, height adjustable stand.

    If you are buying it for TV purpose, better go with Ethernet port, more HDMI ports, Audio out ports. There are Remote PC and Office 365 options. I doubt anyone will ever use them.
